<concept id="_5_1_1_product_vision_and_audience_needs">
    <title>5.1.1 Product Vision and Audience Needs</title>
    <shortdesc>Identify your business objectives, form hypotheses, and understand your potential
        product audience's needs.</shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <p>Identify your business objectives, form hypotheses, and understand your potential product
            audience's needs.<ul id="ul_py1_3ry_pbc">
                <li>
                    <p><b>Objectives:</b> Define why the product exists and what it aims to achieve
                        (general and business goals, KPIs).</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><b>Business Hypotheses:</b> Instead of guessing your visionâ€™s success, create
                        hypotheses. This mindset encourages experimentation and allows for roadmap
                        changes.</p>
                </li>
                <li><b>Target Audience:</b> Understanding audience needs shapes the product. Conduct
                    market analysis, research potential users, and gather feedback. Include elements
                        like:<ul id="ul_gxg_kry_pbc">
                        <li>
                            <p>Demographic characteristics</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Needs and expectations</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Activities and buying habits</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Problems and pain points</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Available technological solutions</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul></li>
            </ul></p>
    </conbody>
</concept>
